./runs/20260529-163436-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:7307:      "note": "The model is answerable to blocked seekers, depression, addiction, burnout, grief, meaning crisis, and achievement-contingent self-worth, while naming clinical and material limits."
./runs/20260529-163436-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:7313:      "note": "The method's self-relationship at completion (confirming, canceling, dissolving) determines how the inferential gap after objectless states is resolved and which clause of the post-gap report receives evidential authority."
./runs/20260529-163436-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:7331:      "note": "The dialogue extended the post-gap model from contemplative objectless states to grief numbness, burnout blankness, and dreamless sleep, but this analogy is untested."
./runs/20260529-163436-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:7379:      "note": "The teaching line ('do not let the first sentence own the whole event') was proposed as applicable to grief, burnout, blackout, dissociation-like withdrawal, and psychedelic dissolution. The full five-category rubric's transfer to non-contemplative populations remains empirically untested. Herman's trauma-recovery model raises a specific objection: ordinary rupture frequently destroys the narrative coherence the grammar framework presupposes."
